status_message:
Thanks again to everyone who made it out to the last show and to all those who were a part of POK over the years. 

We never got this mixed properly, but here's the cleanest version of Modernity we had. We always had a great time playing this one live.

http://pileofkittens.com/music/POK-Modernity.mp3

As we play our final show tonight, we'll be reflecting on all the times we've played together. We get to spend tonight with you, our fans, who have come out to support us whenever you could. For that, we are grateful and appreciative.

Yes, it's true -- Pile of Kittens will be playing our *LAST* NY show at Desmond's Tavern in Midtown this November. Make it a night to remember and come see us off in style.  

21+, cover is $10 at the door, so come on out and support the Pile! We need YOU! (and a bunch of other people)

<3 =^.^=

***Note***
Our timeslot has changed.  We now go on at 10pm!

Current Lineup:

8pm - Side B
9pm - Stretch Cunningham
10pm - Pile of Kittens
link_name: This Kitten's Cooked -- our final show!

status_message: Sad to announce the departure of our bass player Zach. He'll be playing with us until he moves to Michigan later this month. He will be missed and will forever be a Kitten!
Possible gig in CT coming up. Keep it here for more info.
Back in the studio tonight. Can't wait to crank out the tunes!
Back in the studio next week. It's been way too long...
Should be back in the studio rehearsing some new and old stuff soon. Seems like my wrist can handle drumming again. - Tracey
It's Friday, everyone! Now go out and party like some rock stars! You've earned it.

Message from the drummer: Sidelined for a few weeks with this wrist injury, but I hope to come back from it better than ever! Hope to get into the studio this month to record some of our new material and I'm looking forward to playing with the rest of the Kittens soon. - Tracey
Happy 2013! Here's hoping to some upcoming show announcements! =^.^=
Happy Holidays from Pile of Kittens! Hope to see you all at a show in 2013! =^.^=
I just found this from the last Trash Bar Show!

Our very own Zach Lanier won an auction at the Tom Scharpling (of The Best Show on WFMU with Tom Scharpling) and Ted Leo "Hurricane Sandy" relief benefit at The Bell House on Friday -- and got to sing with Ted Leo!
Thanks to all who came out to the show at The Trash Bar last night, and great job by the other bands! =^.^=

Ok Kittens, one last reminder.  We play Trash Bar tomorrow night.  Two new songs, one less turkey.  Come on out!

status_message: Come wipe away the Thanksgiving blues with some post Thanksgiving punk rock!

We're headed back to Trash Bar for a little of the ol' post-Thanksgiving rocking out. Buck up, push through the tryptophan daze, grab a beer (or your beverage of choice), and come join us on Saturday, Nov. 24 in Williamsburg, and give thanks for good times.

$8 at the door.
News. We haz it soon. Stay tuned. =^.^=
We are here. Bring the noise.
Remember kittens, we're playing a free show in Prospect Park tomorrow!  Bring a picnic lunch and join us.
Drum tracking at the Kennel last night in Brooklyn was lots of fun and a total success. Can't wait for everyone to hear the new songs once they're all mixed and ready to go.
Come hang out with us in Prospect Park!

Hey kittens, get ready to be outdoor cats.  We know that our last show ended a little abruptly, so we're making it up to you with an acoustic picnic in the park.  We'll be playing all the hits at the Prospect Park Music Pagoda on what will hopefully be a beautiful late summer afternoon.  Bring a picnic lunch and hang out with us! 

Now on to the karaoke part.  If you have a song that you'd like to sing or play with us, whether it is a PoK original or a cover from your favorite band, let us know in the comments and we'll be ready for you!  Have you always dreamed of singing "La Vida Loca" with the Kittens?  This is your chance!

Here's the link to the Music Pagoda map.  The closest subway stop is the Prospect Park B/Q/S station.
https://maps.google.com/maps?q=Music+Pagoda,+Brooklyn,+New+York,+NY&hl=en&ll=40.662459,-73.964832&spn=0.013315,0.027874&sll=40.697488,-73.979681&sspn=0.851684,1.783905&oq=music+pagoda,+brookly&hnear=Music+Pagoda,+Brooklyn,+Kings,+New+York+11225&t=m&z=16
What better way to spend a hot afternoon than downloading/listening to some Kittens tunes and cranking them, while enjoying some ice cold beverages. Get in the summer spirit! Stay cool, people.

Thank you again everyone for coming out and sorry about the short set. We hope to make it up to all of you this summer. Until then, a little love from Zach and Becca on the mic and some Bouncing Souls
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gAPUyOhZdxo&feature=youtu.be

status_message:
We want to say thanks to everyone who came outfor a great night last night.  We had a lot of fun with so many of our friends and family at the show.  

That said, we're really frustrated with how the set ended, and we want to make sure that all of you get what you paid for, so we're planning on a FREE event this summer to make it up to all of you.  Stay tuned!

Remember Kittens, we play the Studio at Webster Hall on Wednesday evening!  We are almost out of presale tickets, but you can still buy a ticket at the door, or online at http://www.ticketweb.com/t3/sale/SaleEventDetail?dispatch=loadSelectionData&eventId=4611055

status_message:
PoK is following up our successful show at Trash Bar with a bigger, better, furrier gig downstairs at Webster Hall!  We are actually doing presale for this show, so if you'd like to go, get in touch with us and we'll sell you a ticket.  It will be $10 if you buy in advance, and $12 at the door, so it pays to get in on this one ahead of time.  It will be an early show, so don't worry about it being a school night. 

Come on out and support the Pile!  We need YOU! (and a bunch of other people)

Hoping all you kittens enjoy your weekend ahead. Go on, get a little crazy. You've earned it!

If you came out to the show last night at Fat Baby, we thank you! And thanks again to Transcend the Core for their awesomeness and to the other bands who contributed to an awesome night of rock!
Great show at Fat Baby last night!  We had a great time, and we hope you did too.  Thanks to everyone who came out.  We're working on booking more shows, so you'll be hearing from us again soon.
WWW.PILEOFKITTENS.COM. Dig it.

Thursday 2/16 at Fat Baby. We'll be living large.
Ok kittens, we're brewing something up for next week.  Keep your eyes peeled.
Drummer Tracey Andronaco and bass player Zach Lanier, having a pre-show discussion.

Ooops! That last post was deleted by accident. We just wanted to thank everyone who came out on Wednesday night to show their support. It was an awesome show and we had a fun time playing it. We'll be back soon with more shows and more songs! Keep it here for updates. We also have a twitter: @POK_Band. So follow us.
Sorry peeps, we just learned there is a $5 cover for tonight. Head to the back of the bar.  On the plus side there are also tables and chairs (for either siting or throwing)
POK plays Parkside tonight at 10PM! Be there!
Late night of screening new shirts for the show. Some one thought we needed more colors besides just black.

Keep liking our page, people! Doing so will add years to your life. (Not really, but we'd like to think so).
Everyone having a good week so far? I know it's only Monday, but no time like the present. Keep it here and keep it rockin'!

status_message: Sign up, and become a fan on our page. Also, listen to ReverbRadio streaming right from the site. Cool, eh? You might even catch us on there. Listen to the tracks and like 'em from the media player. Show your Kitten love as much as you can! POK thanks you.
Check out our myspace page and like us (if you do, that is). The link to facebook is right on there. And check out our tunes! Show us some support!
POK <3's all of you. Have a great Monday! Back to the grind.
The Kittens want to thank you all for being so patient. We plan on gigging by December. Working in the studio on some new songs. We'll be bringing the 'core to you soon! *Meow*
Happy Belated Halloween to all! Did you do anything crazy to celebrate this year?
Back in the studio tomorrow. Continuing to work on some new tunes.
Trying to book some gigs for the fall in CT. We'll keep you posted on future dates here.
I think it's time to update the band photos. Anyone know of a good photographer who can take some nice shots of us around the city? Candid shots would be a plus.
I think a good cover song for us would be the Cars, 'Just What I Needed.' What do you think?

status_message: Hello, all you little Kittens! Just a reminder that the EP is out. So if you'd like to put in your orders, get in touch here. And by the way, Gaga gets to call all her fans 'Little Monsters,' hence why I'm calling all of you Little Kittens from now on.
PUT YOUR ORDERS IN! I have copies of the Pile of Kittens EP. Let me know the best way to get it to you, and we'll figure out delivery options. - Tracey
'Don't Trust' EP coming out soon. It's all mastered and ready to go. Keep it here to find out how you can score yourself a copy.

is looking for a BASS PLAYER. Sadly, Doug is no longer with the band. If you or anyone else knows of someone who might be interested in coming out and auditioning with us, please get in touch. Thanks! And keep it rockin'!
We've been on hiatus for quite sometime. But will be keeping you all posted on when the EP is complete and released. Check back for updates!
We played Popeye's last night.  No Chicken, but some delicous rock and roll.  We're taking a break for a few months for some songwriting and baby rearing, but we'll be back soon!
